   "author_association" : "MEMBER",
   "body" : "`g_rpc_node` is an alias for the current node context. It would be nice to pass in the node context into each rpc method somehow and remove the g_rpc_node global.\r\n\r\nNot sure how to do this, but here is a hint: https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/17407#discussion_r346488421\r\n\r\n> One way `g_rpc_node` might go away is adding a `std::any context` member to `JSONRPCRequest` assigned to the node context, and having functions like `EnsureMempool` take `request` arguments and pull the context from the request.",
